**Selenium Setup and Test in Command Line (Step by Step)**

###  Step 1 – Check Python

```bash
python --version
```


### 🔹 Step 2 – Check pip

```bash
pip --version
```

If it says “not found,” then run:

```bash
python -m ensurepip --default-pip
```

---

### Step 3 – Install Selenium and WebDriver Manager

```bash
pip install selenium webdriver-manager
```

---

###  Step 4 – Create a test file

In Command Prompt (Windows) or Terminal (Mac/Linux):

```bash
notepad test_selenium.py
```

️

```python
# test_selenium.py
from selenium import webdriver
from selenium.webdriver.common.by import By
from selenium.webdriver.chrome.service import Service
from webdriver_manager.chrome import ChromeDriverManager
import time

# setup Chrome
driver = webdriver.Chrome(service=Service(ChromeDriverManager().install()))

# open website
driver.get("https://www.google.com")

# print title
print("Page title:", driver.title)

# wait few seconds
time.sleep(3)

# close browser
driver.quit()


### 🔹 Step 5 – Run the test

```bash
python test_selenium.py
```


### 🔹 Step 6 – (If want Headless mode)

Edit the file and add this before `driver = webdriver.Chrome(...)`:

```python
from selenium.webdriver.chrome.options import Options
options = Options()
options.add_argument("--headless=new")
driver = webdriver.Chrome(service=Service(ChromeDriverManager().install()), options=options)
```

Then rerun:

```bash
python test_selenium.py
```
